	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>21. Nov&#47;56</date></p>
				<p>My dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have been requested by our friend<lb/> <persName>Mr. Selig Newman</persName> to subject your good offices<lb/> and advice to help him to obtain subscribers for<lb/> an American Edition of his Hebrew Grammar</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This grammar has pressed through several<lb/> editions and is favorably known in <placeName>england</placeName>.  I my<lb/>self have used it in the Hebrew National School<lb/> <placeName>Birmingham</placeName>&#44; and it is generally considered<lb/> as best adapted for Hebrew Schools.  <persName>Mr. N&#39;s</persName> long<lb/> experience as a teacher has taught him what<lb/> an Heb. Grammr ought to be&#44; so that he has produced<lb/> one&#44; well digested in its system clear in its rules<lb/> brief but distinct in the directions&#44; and condensing<lb/> within a moderate number of pages&#44; every thing the<lb/> student needs.  The <placeName>London</placeName> J&#58; Chron. For <date>Novr. 1854</date> also<lb/> speaks of it in the highest terms.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Newmans</persName> requests to you are 1.  That you<lb/> would please favorably to <sic>anounce</sic> his gramr in<lb/> the Occident.  2. That you would afford him the<lb/> benefit of your advice as to the best mode of going<lb/> to work&#44; in order to obtain subscribers.  3. Where he<lb/> can best get it printed and is likely to find a<lb/> publisher.  Any further suggestions will be thankfully recd.<lb/> His address is <persName>S. Newman</persName>. <placeName>218. 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Avenue</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours my Dr Sir&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Very Sincerely</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M J Raphall Dr</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Pha.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Turn Over</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>The Grammar will contain about<lb/> 100 pages.  What ought he to charge<lb/> for it&#63;</p>
		</body>
